### Set 3: Iterative Refinement and Hallucination Mitigation

#### Task 3.1: Iterative Refinement with Context Windows (10 minutes)

**Objective**: Refine prompt design to work even when the research paper is longer than the model‚Äôs context limit.

**Steps**:

1. Refine your Task 2.2 Few-Shot prompt by adding the following context management strategies: a) instruct the model to summarize smaller chunks if the paper size exceeds the context window and b) introduce variables (e.g., [chunk1] and [chunk2]) to represent split parts of the paper. 

Following the exact same format as given below, for each of the sections entiled "Introduction", "Backround", and "Results" provide a 50-word expert summary and a 50-word layperson summary of the key points respective to each section. If the paper size exeeds the context window, then split it into chunks enitled ([chunk 1], [chunk 2], etc..) to represent the split parts of the paper and summarize each chunk seperatly in the same format as the original, otherwise stick to the original format. Again, Do not deviate from the following format: 

Section: Model Architecture
üë®‚Äçüî¨ Expert Summary (50 words)
The Transformer architecture comprises stacked encoder and decoder layers built from multi-head self-attention and position-wise feed-forward networks. It replaces recurrence with parallelizable attention mechanisms, incorporates residual connections and layer normalization, and uses sinusoidal positional encodings to capture token order, enabling efficient and scalable sequence transduction.
üßë‚Äçüè´ Layperson Summary (50 words)
The Transformer is a new kind of AI model that reads and writes sentences using attention instead of older methods like memory loops. It looks at all words at once, learns patterns faster, and uses math tricks to understand word order. This makes it quicker and better at translating languages




2. Test, save transcript link via shareable link. 

https://copilot.microsoft.com/shares/LTszqzMYuQ8PBP3Vown6C

**Deliverables**:

- Refined prompt
- Transcript link

#### Task 3.2: Hallucination-Proofing Your Prompts (10 minutes)

**Objective**: Strengthen the prompts you wrote in earlier tasks by adding clear instructions that reduce hallucinations.  

**Steps**:  

1. Look back at the prompts you created in Set 1 and Set 2.  
2. Choose **two prompts** you wrote.  
3. Rewrite each one to include at least **one hallucination-mitigation instruction**, for example:  
   - *‚ÄúOnly include information explicitly present in the paper.‚Äù*  

 
1.Following the exact same format as given below, for each of the sections entiled "Introduction", "Backround", and "Results" provide a 50-word expert summary and a 50-word layperson summary of the key points respective to each section. Make sure to include only information explicitly stated in the text: do not assume, make up or draw on additional sources in your summaries.Do not deviate from the following format: 

Section: Model Architecture
üë®‚Äçüî¨ Expert Summary (50 words)
The Transformer architecture comprises stacked encoder and decoder layers built from multi-head self-attention and position-wise feed-forward networks. It replaces recurrence with parallelizable attention mechanisms, incorporates residual connections and layer normalization, and uses sinusoidal positional encodings to capture token order, enabling efficient and scalable sequence transduction.
üßë‚Äçüè´ Layperson Summary (50 words)
The Transformer is a new kind of AI model that reads and writes sentences using attention instead of older methods like memory loops. It looks at all words at once, learns patterns faster, and uses math tricks to understand word order. This makes it quicker and better at translating languages 


2) To summarize the reasearch paper {Paper_title}, first identify the main argument, then the supporting points then finally how it might relate to the paper's overall thesis, explaining your reasoning for each one along the way. After for the section entilted {section_title} provide two short summaries. One 50 word expert summary and one 50 word layperson summary of the main points of that specific section. Then for the section entilted {section_title} create a mini glossary of {term_count} key terms, with each of them having a one sentence description to provide clarity for readers. In making these summaries only summarize content given in each section, do not drawn on any piror knowledge or information on the subject.


4. Test one of your rewritten prompts with *Attention Is All You Need*. Save the transcript link.   

